org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.activity.support
Class AeCompInfo

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.activity.support.AeCompInfo
Direct Known Subclasses:
AeCoordinatorCompInfo
public class AeCompInfo
extends java.lang.Object

An AeCompInfo object represents a single successful execution of a scope activity. It contains a reference to the scope that completed, a variable snapshot object to record the state of all of the variables, and a collection of any child AeCompInfo objects that may have been created by enclosed scopes. This information is reported back to the scope's enclosing scope in case the scope needs to be compensated.

hasEnabledCoordinatedChildren

public boolean hasEnabledCoordinatedChildren()
Returns true if any of the enclosed (child) AeCoordinatorCompInfo objects are enabled. A CompoInfo object is initially enabled and disabled after being executed (compensated). A disabled comp info should not be used to avoid REPEATED_COMPENSATION faults.

Returns:
true if any of the comp info objects have not been run already.

compensationComplete

public void compensationComplete()

removeCompensatedScopes

protected void removeCompensatedScopes()
Removes any enclosed comp info references that have been compensated. This method should be called when the references are no longer reachable, which would be at the end of a compensationHandler's execution.
